  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\nI created a storage class with provisioner set to my CSI driver, and with mountOptions set to a non-empty value.\r\n\r\nI expected Kubernetes to send the mount options to my CSI driver in the mountFlags field of the CSI RPC, but the field was empty.\r\n\r\nReproduction:\r\n1) Install kubernetes\r\n2) Install any CSI driver\r\n3) Create a storage class, with the provisioner set to the installed CSI driver's name, and the mount options set to something.\r\n4) Create a PVC, and attach it to a pod\r\n5) Note that the pod either fails to start up, or if it does start, the mount options are ignored.\r\n",
